01:29.567 --> 01:31.787
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:31.917 --> 01:33.571
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:33.702 --> 01:35.573
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

01:35.704 --> 01:37.488
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.619 --> 01:40.970
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.101 --> 01:43.755
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.886 --> 01:46.628
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:54.766 --> 01:56.638
BAYWTACH

02:01.991 --> 02:03.732
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

02:03.862 --> 02:06.996
"FATHER'S DAY"

03:27.032 --> 03:29.121
IT'S MOMENTS LIKE THIS
YOU NEVER FORGET, PAL.

03:30.819 --> 03:32.429
I REMEMBER COMING OUT HERE ONCE,

03:32.560 --> 03:34.649
ON FATHER'S DAY WITH MY DAD.

03:37.260 --> 03:38.740
I WAS 14 YEARS OLD.

03:39.306 --> 03:41.395
GRANDPA TRIED SURFING? NO WAY.

03:41.525 --> 03:42.961
[LAUGHING]

03:43.092 --> 03:45.007
HE SAID HE'D TRY IT FOR ME.

03:45.834 --> 03:47.444
WANTED TO SEE WHY I WOULD GET UP

03:47.575 --> 03:49.316
BEFORE DAWN TO COME OUT HERE.

03:50.055 --> 03:51.056
SO WHAT HAPPENED?

03:51.187 --> 03:52.841
HE DIDN'T GET IT.

03:52.971 --> 03:56.410
PADDLE OUT, RIDE IN, OUT,
IN, OUT, IN. WHAT'S THE POINT?

03:57.193 --> 03:58.760
AH, THE FEELING YOU GET.

03:58.890 --> 04:01.676
GRANDPA DIDN'T DEAL
WITH HIS FEELINGS TOO MUCH, PAL.

04:01.806 --> 04:03.330
BUT WE DO, DON'T WE?

04:03.460 --> 04:04.548
READY TO FEEL THE RUSH?

04:05.288 --> 04:06.463
YOU BET!

04:06.724 --> 04:09.031
DAD, HAPPY FATHER'S DAY.

04:09.161 --> 04:12.121
THANKS, PAL. I'M GLAD
I CAN SPEND IT WITH YOU.

04:13.209 --> 04:15.167
OUTSIDE! LET'S GO!

04:20.041 --> 04:21.130
ALL RIGHT!

04:22.349 --> 04:23.654
YEAH, DAD!

04:26.004 --> 04:28.703
YEAH! WOO!

04:34.012 --> 04:37.015
[UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING]

04:54.729 --> 04:58.515
[ENERGETIC MUSIC PLAYING]

05:14.226 --> 05:16.011
WHAT? WHAT IS IT?

05:16.141 --> 05:18.056
KEEP OUR BEACHES CLEAN

05:18.709 --> 05:19.754
LOGAN?

05:20.581 --> 05:22.887
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

05:49.958 --> 05:51.263
LOGAN?

05:52.352 --> 05:54.484
HEY! LOGAN?

05:55.572 --> 05:56.660
[SIGHING]

05:57.226 --> 05:58.532
WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

06:03.667 --> 06:04.799
I DON'T KNOW.

06:26.603 --> 06:28.257
I'LL GET RIGHT ON IT. THANK YOU.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.302
MATT, THERE'S SOME RIPS
PULLING SOUTH OF THE JETTY.

06:30.433 --> 06:31.869
I WANT YOU TO GO OUT
AND BACK UP LOGAN.

06:32.000 --> 06:33.088
GIVE HIM SOME HELP
OUT THERE, OKAY?

06:33.218 --> 06:34.306
OKAY.

06:34.785 --> 06:36.613
HEY, HOW'D IT GO LAST NIGHT?

06:37.527 --> 06:39.007
IT DIDN'T.

06:39.137 --> 06:41.357
I THOUGHT YOUR DAD WAS FLYING IN
FOR FATHER'S DAY.

06:41.488 --> 06:43.838
HE SAID HE WAS GONNA STOP BY
ON HIS WAY BACK FROM FRANCE,

06:43.968 --> 06:46.057
BUT, UH, HIS MEETING
GOT PUSHED UP

06:46.188 --> 06:47.276
AND HE DIDN'T HAVE ENOUGH TIME.

06:48.277 --> 06:51.846
BUT HE CALLED FROM THE PLANE
AND SAID TO LOOK UP AND WAVE.

06:51.976 --> 06:53.935
BUSINESS BEFORE PLEASURE, HUH?

06:54.065 --> 06:55.240
BUSINESS BEFORE EVERYTHING.

06:56.198 --> 06:57.895
THAT'S MY DAD'S LIFELONG MOTTO.

06:59.157 --> 07:01.464
HEY, BUT WHATEVER
MAKES THE MAN HAPPY.

07:02.117 --> 07:03.466
WON'T YOU COME CELEBRATE

07:03.597 --> 07:04.902
FATHER'S DAY WITH MITCH,
AND HOBIE, AND ME?

07:05.033 --> 07:06.164
I MEAN, MITCH'S MOM'S COMING
TO DINNER.

07:06.295 --> 07:07.818
HOBIE'S COOKING. IT'LL BE GREAT.

07:08.036 --> 07:09.777
I THINK I'LL PASS.

07:09.907 --> 07:12.301
THE LAST TIME HOBIE COOKED,
MY MOUTH WAS ON FIRE FOR A WEEK.

07:12.823 --> 07:13.607
BUT THANKS.

07:13.737 --> 07:14.651
SEE YA.

07:18.394 --> 07:20.091
[COUGHING]

07:20.222 --> 07:23.181
UH, HOBIE, THAT,
THAT WAS DELICIOUS.

07:23.312 --> 07:25.183
THANKS.
IT WASN'T TOO SPICY, WAS IT?

07:25.314 --> 07:26.402
OH, NO, NO.

07:26.533 --> 07:28.491
NO. IT WAS GREAT.

07:28.622 --> 07:29.536
WHAT'S FOR DESSERT?

07:29.666 --> 07:30.841
ICE CREAM.

07:30.972 --> 07:32.626
OH, THANK GOD.

07:32.756 --> 07:34.279
JALAPENO FLAVOR.

07:34.410 --> 07:35.193
[WHEEZING]

07:35.324 --> 07:36.238
JUST KIDDING.

07:36.978 --> 07:40.372
[SNIFFLING]

07:40.503 --> 07:41.983
I GOT SOMETHIN' FOR YA, DAD.

07:42.113 --> 07:43.550
-OH, ISN'T THAT NICE.
-OH, OH.

07:43.680 --> 07:45.116
-HAPPY FATHER'S DAY.
-THANKS.

07:45.247 --> 07:46.814
[COUGHING]

07:48.642 --> 07:50.818
HEY, LOOK AT THIS.

07:50.948 --> 07:52.472
A FISH TIE.

07:53.168 --> 07:55.300
-IT'S A MACKEREL.
-OH!

07:55.431 --> 07:57.955
I DOESN'T SMELL LIKE A MACKEREL,
THANK GOODNESS.

07:58.086 --> 07:58.956
IT'S PURE SILK.

07:59.087 --> 08:00.784
THAT'S GREAT, HOBIE.

08:00.915 --> 08:03.395
IT GOES WITH MY SHIRT, HUH?
THANKS, PAL. I'LL WEAR IT.

08:03.526 --> 08:06.094
I HAVE SOMETHING
FOR YOUR DAD, AS WELL.

08:07.051 --> 08:10.054
I WAS CLEANING OUT
YOUR FATHER'S CLOSET LAST MONTH

08:10.185 --> 08:12.709
AND I FOUND THIS IN THE BOTTOM
OF A DRAWER.

08:17.235 --> 08:20.500
FATHER'S DAY 1988?
WHAT'S IN HERE?

08:20.630 --> 08:22.502
WELL, IT'S SOMETHING YOUR FATHER

08:22.632 --> 08:24.721
OBVIOUSLY WANTED TO GIVE YOU
ON THAT FATHER'S DAY,

08:24.852 --> 08:27.942
BUT, YOU KNOW, FOR SOME REASON,
HE NEVER DID.

08:28.072 --> 08:30.422
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT LIKE
TO OPEN IT NOW.

08:32.250 --> 08:34.121
FATHER'S DAY 1988

08:35.515 --> 08:37.081
GO ON, DAD, OPEN IT.

08:37.212 --> 08:39.169
YEAH, MITCH, OPEN IT.
I WANNA SEE WHAT'S INSIDE.

08:39.301 --> 08:43.044
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

08:43.174 --> 08:45.307
NO, NO, NO.
IS YOUR NAME ON HERE?

08:45.437 --> 08:46.917
-NO.
-OKAY.

08:47.048 --> 08:48.702
OKAY, JUST LEAVE ME ALONE.

08:50.094 --> 08:51.966
I'LL OPEN IT WHEN I'M READY.

08:56.448 --> 08:58.450
[SIGHING]

09:00.714 --> 09:03.281
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

09:27.436 --> 09:31.005
[DISTANT BREATH]

09:51.503 --> 09:53.375
WHAT DO YOU SEE
WHEN YOU LOOK INTO THE FIRE?

09:55.290 --> 09:56.857
SOMETHING IN MY MEMORY.

09:57.901 --> 09:59.294
[SIGHING]

09:59.424 --> 10:01.557
AS SOON AS I TRY TO FOCUS,
IT GOES AWAY.

10:02.689 --> 10:04.342
WHAT DOES IT START OUT AS?

10:07.911 --> 10:09.260
FIRE.

10:13.438 --> 10:14.570
FLAME.

10:18.443 --> 10:19.923
WHAT DO YOU FEEL?

10:22.883 --> 10:24.232
FEAR.

10:25.494 --> 10:28.105
[INDISTINCT SPEECH]

10:31.108 --> 10:33.110
[CAROLINE] WHAT?
LOGAN, WHAT IS IT?

10:33.241 --> 10:34.285
I DON'T KNOW.

10:35.983 --> 10:38.899
WHEN I START THINKING ABOUT IT,
ALL I SEE IS THE FIRE.

10:41.162 --> 10:43.817
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

10:46.602 --> 10:48.256
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE AFRAID.

10:49.823 --> 10:51.520
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE AFRAID
OF ANYTHING.

11:06.100 --> 11:09.233
[CHEERY MUSIC PLAYING]

11:20.375 --> 11:22.638
WE WERE SUPPOSE TO WORK OUT
TOGETHER THIS MORNING.

11:23.117 --> 11:25.162
YEAH, I KNOW. I'M SORRY.

11:26.729 --> 11:28.470
HEY, YOU HAVEN'T OPENED
THIS YET, HUH?

11:29.819 --> 11:30.907
NO.

11:31.647 --> 11:33.562
WELL, LOOK AT THIS.
THIS WAS 1988.

11:33.693 --> 11:37.392
THIS WAS BURIED IN
MY DAD'S CLOSET SINCE 1988.

11:39.002 --> 11:40.438
WHY DIDN'T HE GIVE IT
TO ME THEN?

11:41.135 --> 11:43.441
WELL, MAYBE IF YOU OPEN IT UP,
YOU'LL FIND OUT.

11:45.705 --> 11:46.749
LOOK, I'LL OPEN IT.

11:46.880 --> 11:48.446
NO. NO.

11:48.577 --> 11:50.622
WHAT ARE YOU AFRAID IS IN THERE?

11:52.189 --> 11:53.713
STEPHANIE, THIS SAYS,

11:53.843 --> 11:58.152
"TO MITCH, MY SON,
WITH LOVE AND RESPECT. DAD."

12:00.284 --> 12:01.764
HE NEVER CALLED ME SON.

12:02.896 --> 12:06.726
HE NEVER SIGNED ANYTHING TO ME
WITH LOVE AND RESPECT.

12:08.162 --> 12:11.992
IT WAS ALWAYS
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DAD.

12:12.296 --> 12:14.951
MERRY CHRISTMAS, DAD.

12:15.691 --> 12:17.649
WELL, THEN, IT MUST BE SOMETHING
VERY SPECIAL.

12:17.780 --> 12:19.173
SO JUST OPEN IT.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.479
[INHALING SHARPLY]

12:23.133 --> 12:25.179
YEAH, I BETTER WAIT
'TIL AFTER WORK.

12:25.309 --> 12:27.834
I CAN'T AFFORD TO BE LESS
THAN A HUNDRED PERCENT FOCUSED.

12:27.964 --> 12:29.923
AND I HAVE A FEELING
THAT WHATEVER'S IN HERE

12:30.053 --> 12:32.403
IS GONNA BE DISTRACTING,
TO SAY THE LEAST.

12:33.013 --> 12:34.579
YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANT ME
TO OPEN IT?

12:36.538 --> 12:38.192
JUST THOUGHT I'D ASK.

12:40.107 --> 12:42.065
[INDISTINCT SPEAKING]

12:43.240 --> 12:44.285
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA. HEY, MITCH.

12:44.415 --> 12:45.895
WOO. MITCH!

12:48.202 --> 12:49.507
[GRUNTING]

12:49.638 --> 12:50.987
DO YOU MIND DROPPIN' ME
AT MY TOWER?

12:51.118 --> 12:52.946
-NO PROBLEM.
-I'M ONLY A TAD BIT LATE. SORRY.

12:59.082 --> 13:00.736
SO HOW IS YOUR FATHER'S DAY?

13:00.867 --> 13:02.564
I DON'T KNOW, YET. HOW IS YOURS?

13:02.869 --> 13:06.350
I DIDN'T KNOW MY DAD AND I'M
NOT ONE, AS FAR AS I KNOW.

13:06.742 --> 13:08.657
SO IT'S NOT A DAY I CELEBRATE.

13:08.788 --> 13:10.354
[MAN OVER RADIO] TWO-NINE-FIVE TO TWO-ONE-SEVEN LINCOLN,

13:10.485 --> 13:12.313
PLEASE RESPOND.  CODE THREE TO TOWER 18 MALIBU.

13:12.443 --> 13:13.923
BOAT OUTSIDE SURF LINE.

13:15.011 --> 13:18.580
TEN-FOUR, TWO-NINE-FIVE. THIS IS
TWO-ONE-SEVEN L, IN ROUTE.

13:19.842 --> 13:21.104
LET'S GO.

13:23.280 --> 13:24.804
[WOMAN] HELP!

13:26.022 --> 13:29.417
[SIREN WAILING]

13:36.293 --> 13:37.599
HELP!

13:37.729 --> 13:39.253
ALL RIGHT,
TAKE THE PADDLE BOARD.

13:45.607 --> 13:46.869
[WOMAN COUGHING]

13:51.787 --> 13:53.397
JUST HURRY UP!

13:53.528 --> 13:56.183
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

14:00.491 --> 14:02.842
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

14:19.510 --> 14:20.903
[WOMAN] HELP!

14:26.126 --> 14:27.605
-[MAN] LEAVE IT!
-[WOMAN] OKAY.

14:31.218 --> 14:34.308
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

14:39.226 --> 14:40.662
[COUGHING]

14:43.839 --> 14:45.493
LOGAN, MOVE IT! LET'S GO!

14:46.015 --> 14:48.626
[WOMAN] HELP! HELP!

14:49.453 --> 14:50.759
[GRUNTING]

14:54.458 --> 14:55.895
IN HERE!

14:57.374 --> 14:58.549
IN HERE!

15:02.945 --> 15:04.425
[GRUNTING]

15:06.818 --> 15:09.909
[COUGHING]

15:18.613 --> 15:20.876
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

15:21.833 --> 15:24.053
[MITCH] HE'S STUCK.
WE CAN'T GET HIM OUT.

15:24.184 --> 15:26.882
[PANTING]

15:41.288 --> 15:44.291
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

15:49.470 --> 15:51.994
LOS ANGELES COUNTY
LIFEGUARD

15:55.345 --> 15:57.739
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

15:58.305 --> 16:00.394
[GRUNTING]

16:09.490 --> 16:11.013
[SIGHING]

16:12.841 --> 16:15.975
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

16:16.976 --> 16:18.716
BAYWATCH

16:22.111 --> 16:23.591
MY SON'S IN THERE!

16:23.721 --> 16:26.942
IT'S OKAY! IT'S OKAY!

16:27.073 --> 16:28.857
I'LL GO GET HIM!

16:29.901 --> 16:31.381
GO ON!

16:35.690 --> 16:38.998
MY BABY! MY SON'S IN THERE!

16:43.785 --> 16:46.527
[PANTING]

16:51.967 --> 16:54.187
[MAN] OUR BABY!

16:54.578 --> 16:56.493
[YELLING]

16:56.624 --> 16:59.627
IT'S OKAY! IT'S OKAY! IT'S OKAY!

16:59.757 --> 17:01.368
OUR BABY'S IN THERE!

17:08.243 --> 17:11.030
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

17:17.862 --> 17:20.517
-MY BABY!
-LOGAN, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:21.474 --> 17:22.824
MITCH!

17:22.954 --> 17:25.305
I'M GOING BACK IN!

17:27.089 --> 17:30.223
MITCH! GET OUT! GET OUT!

17:33.661 --> 17:36.359
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

17:38.883 --> 17:41.799
LOGAN, WAKE UP!

17:41.930 --> 17:45.151
MITCH, HURRY UP! GET OUT!

17:56.553 --> 17:58.120
[PANTING]

18:05.649 --> 18:07.260
LOGAN, WAKE UP!

18:07.390 --> 18:08.957
GO GET THE BABY!

18:09.088 --> 18:11.177
LOGAN, WAKE UP!

18:12.265 --> 18:16.834
MITCH! GET OUT! HURRY UP!

18:16.965 --> 18:21.839
[WOMAN] PLEASE!
SOMEONE RESCUE MY BABY?

18:24.538 --> 18:26.757
[WOMAN CRYING]

18:28.455 --> 18:32.111
MITCH! MITCH, GET OUT! HURRY!

18:34.243 --> 18:36.550
-HURRY UP!
-OH, MY GOD!

18:36.680 --> 18:38.595
LOGAN, WAKE UP!

18:38.726 --> 18:40.162
[MAN OVER RADIO]
SCARAB ONE, PLEASE REPORT

18:40.293 --> 18:41.468
OUR RESCUE STATUS, OVER.

18:43.600 --> 18:45.124
[WOMAN CRYING]

18:45.254 --> 18:46.951
[BABY CRYING]

18:47.387 --> 18:49.128
[WOMAN] THERE HE IS!
THERE HE IS!

18:49.258 --> 18:50.825
THERE HE IS!

18:54.133 --> 18:56.918
-THERE HE IS! THERE HE IS!
-YOU GOT HIM.

18:57.048 --> 18:58.137
[BABY CRYING]

18:58.267 --> 18:59.486
ALL RIGHT, MITCH!

18:59.616 --> 19:02.184
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

19:03.925 --> 19:06.580
[MATT] LOGAN, WAKE UP!
GO GET THE BABY!

19:06.710 --> 19:08.538
[WOMAN CRYING]

19:09.452 --> 19:11.062
[BABY CRYING]

19:11.324 --> 19:13.674
MITCH, HERE. GIVE HIM TO ME.

19:17.460 --> 19:19.636
-YOU ALL RIGHT?
-YEAH, I'M ALL RIGHT.

19:19.767 --> 19:22.291
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

19:37.306 --> 19:38.916
WHAT WAS GOIN' ON
WITH YOU OUT THERE?

19:39.352 --> 19:41.005
NOTHING.

19:41.136 --> 19:42.572
-YOU WERE FREAKED. WHY?
-IT'S NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

19:42.703 --> 19:44.183
IF I CAN'T COUNT
ON YOU IN A RESCUE,

19:44.313 --> 19:46.228
THEN IT BECOMES MY BUSINESS.

19:46.663 --> 19:47.925
I WANT AN ANSWER.

19:48.056 --> 19:50.537
YEAH? WELL, SO THE HELL DO I.

19:54.323 --> 19:57.674
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

20:20.871 --> 20:22.133
YOU OKAY?

20:22.264 --> 20:23.874
NO, NOT VERY.

20:27.487 --> 20:28.705
I SPOKE TO MATT.

20:35.973 --> 20:37.323
YOU WANNA TALK ABOUT IT?

20:41.240 --> 20:42.763
I WAS PADDLING OUT TO THE BOAT.

20:45.374 --> 20:47.246
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

20:47.376 --> 20:49.726
THEN, ALL OF A SUDDEN, IT WAS
LIKE I WAS SOMEWHERE ELSE.

20:50.423 --> 20:54.078
SOME OTHER FIRE, SOME
OTHER PLACE. ANOTHER BOAT.

20:54.731 --> 20:57.038
I SAW IT IN MY HEAD LIKE IT
WAS RIGHT THERE IN FRONT OF ME.

20:58.866 --> 21:00.868
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHERE
THESE THOUGHTS ARE COMING FROM?

21:00.998 --> 21:02.522
THEY'RE COMING FROM IN HERE.

21:06.003 --> 21:07.222
WHERE ELSE DO THINK?

21:09.180 --> 21:12.401
I THINK THAT IT'S A MEMORY.

21:13.924 --> 21:15.578
I THINK THAT'S IT'S SOMETHING
THAT HAPPENED TO YOU

21:16.362 --> 21:18.146
A LONG TIME AGO AND IT'S BEING
TRIGGER NOW BECAUSE OF THE FIRE.

21:18.277 --> 21:20.235
SOMETHING TOO PAINFUL
TO REMEMBER, IS THAT IT?

21:20.366 --> 21:22.237
SO I'M BURYING IT IN MY BRAIN?

21:22.629 --> 21:24.195
I KNOW SOMEBODY
WHO COULD HELP YOU

21:24.326 --> 21:25.893
FIGURE IT OUT,
IF THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

21:26.894 --> 21:29.418
A HEADSHRINKER?
IS THAT WHAT I NEED?

21:31.333 --> 21:32.769
HE'S A HYPNOTIST.

21:34.249 --> 21:35.903
I COULD CALL TO MAKE
AN APPOINTMENT.

21:40.168 --> 21:42.518
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

21:56.880 --> 21:58.273
HEY, DAD. SO WHAT WAS IN IT?

21:58.708 --> 22:00.275
UH, I DON'T KNOW, YET.

22:01.537 --> 22:03.496
WELL, YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT

22:03.626 --> 22:05.628
THAT WE MIGHT AS WELL
ALL BE TOGETHER, YOU KNOW.

22:05.759 --> 22:07.195
OH, BUT HE DIDN'T
MAKE IT FOR US.

22:07.326 --> 22:08.805
HE MADE IT FOR YOU, MITCH.

22:08.936 --> 22:09.893
MADE IT?

22:11.460 --> 22:13.027
YOU KNOW
WHAT'S IN HERE, DON'T YOU?

22:13.157 --> 22:14.811
OF COURSE I DO.

22:14.942 --> 22:17.205
DON'T YOU THINK I KNEW
EVERYTHING ABOUT YOUR FATHER,

22:17.336 --> 22:19.163
AND HE KNEW EVERYTHING ABOUT ME?

22:19.468 --> 22:21.340
WHEN YOU OPEN THIS,

22:21.470 --> 22:23.429
YOU'RE GOING TO FIND,
YOU KNOW, A LOT MORE

22:23.559 --> 22:25.518
ABOUT YOUR FATHER
THAN YOU THOUGHT.

22:28.521 --> 22:29.522
ALL RIGHT.

22:30.871 --> 22:33.221
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

22:56.940 --> 23:00.030
MITCHELL BUCHANNON. LIFEGUARD.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.561
OH, NO WAY!

23:09.170 --> 23:11.564
GRANDPA MADE A SCRAPBOOK
OF YOU AS A LIFEGUARD?

23:11.694 --> 23:14.305
OH, NOT JUST A SCRAPBOOK.

23:14.436 --> 23:16.090
OH, SEE.

23:16.220 --> 23:19.049
ISN'T IT BEAUTIFUL THE WAY
IT'S LAID OUT AND MOUNTED?

23:19.310 --> 23:21.835
AND THERE'S A SENSE OF DESIGN
AND CONTINUITY

23:21.965 --> 23:25.578
THAT YOUR GRANDFATHER INVESTED
IN EVERYTHING HE CREATED.

23:26.840 --> 23:28.058
ISN'T IT WONDERFUL?

23:30.887 --> 23:32.498
DARLING, WHAT'S THE MATTER?

23:32.628 --> 23:34.325
DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

23:34.456 --> 23:35.762
BUT DARLING--

23:35.892 --> 23:37.285
DAD DIDN'T WANT ME
TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

23:38.460 --> 23:41.202
BUT HIS FEELINGS CHANGED.
YOU KNOW THAT.

23:41.332 --> 23:44.727
NOT 'TIL THE END, MOM.
NOT 'TIL THE END.

23:45.380 --> 23:46.642
DID YOU DO THIS OR DID HE?

23:47.730 --> 23:51.081
IT WAS YOUR FATHER'S IDEA
AND IT'S HIS WORK.

23:51.778 --> 23:53.736
OH, WHY, HE'D SIT UP SOMETIMES

23:53.867 --> 23:55.346
UNTIL 3:00
IN THE MORNING AT NIGHT,

23:55.477 --> 23:58.915
JUST CUTTING OUT
THE RIGHT BORDER TO FRAME

23:59.046 --> 24:03.006
A RESCUE CARD
WITH YOUR NAME ON IT.

24:04.834 --> 24:05.835
WHY?

24:05.966 --> 24:07.489
BECAUSE HE WAS PROUD OF YOU.

24:07.620 --> 24:09.622
-HE WAS NEVER PROUD OF ME.
-DAD.

24:09.752 --> 24:11.754
HE WAS VERY PROUD OF YOU, MITCH.

24:11.885 --> 24:13.103
THEN WHY DIDN'T HE TELL ME?

24:14.627 --> 24:16.063
-BECAUSE HE COULDN'T.
-WHY NOT?

24:21.024 --> 24:22.591
HE DIDN'T WANT TO ENCOURAGE YOU.

24:24.288 --> 24:26.421
ENCOURAGE ME?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKIN' ABOUT?

24:28.162 --> 24:31.905
AL WAS VERY PROUD
TO BE YOUR FATHER.

24:32.035 --> 24:34.298
HE'D SHOW THIS BOOK TO EVERYONE
AND HE'D SAY,

24:35.561 --> 24:36.953
"THAT'S MY SON."

24:39.478 --> 24:41.741
"HE'S A BRILLIANT LIFEGUARD NOW,
BUT SOMEDAY,

24:42.568 --> 24:45.005
HE'S GOING TO BE AN EVEN MORE
BRILLIANT ARCHITECT."

24:47.007 --> 24:49.749
"AND WHEN THAT DAY COMES,
I'M GOING TO GIVE HIM THIS BOOK

24:50.401 --> 24:52.491
SO HE'LL HAVE
SOME BEAUTIFUL MEMORIES

24:52.621 --> 24:54.057
OF HIS DAYS ON THE BEACH."

25:07.462 --> 25:08.507
[CHUCKLING]

25:09.290 --> 25:11.205
MY MEDAL OF VALOR.

25:15.470 --> 25:16.515
RESCUE CARD.

25:20.170 --> 25:21.868
AND MY PATCHES.

25:25.698 --> 25:26.655
AH, HERE WE GO.

25:28.222 --> 25:29.266
MY PROMOTION.

25:31.486 --> 25:33.314
THAT'S WHY HE STOPPED IN 1988.

25:37.405 --> 25:38.841
WHY?

25:38.972 --> 25:40.626
BECAUSE THAT WAS THE YEAR
I MADE THE DECISION

25:40.756 --> 25:42.932
TO BECOME A FULL TIME
LIFEGUARD LIEUTENANT.

25:44.717 --> 25:46.501
AND THE YEAR
THAT DAD FINALLY GAVE UP

25:46.632 --> 25:48.198
HIS DREAM OF ME
BEING AN ARCHITECT.

25:49.722 --> 25:51.071
HE LOVED YOU, MITCH.

25:54.770 --> 25:55.945
I KNOW HE DID, MOM.

25:56.990 --> 25:57.860
I KNOW THAT.

26:00.080 --> 26:01.081
I JUST--

26:02.473 --> 26:04.737
I JUST WISH HE'D GIVEN IT
TO ME THEN, YOU KNOW.

26:05.607 --> 26:07.435
DON'T REMEMBER
HIS FAULTS, MITCH.

26:08.088 --> 26:09.698
REMEMBER HIS LOVE.

26:12.832 --> 26:14.573
[SNIFFLING]

26:28.151 --> 26:30.371
NOW FOCUS YOUR ENTIRE
CONCENTRATION ON THE FLAME.

26:32.286 --> 26:34.244
NOW LET YOUR EYES SLOWLY CLOSE.

26:41.208 --> 26:43.950
CONTINUE FOCUSING ON THE
INTERNAL IMAGE OF THE FLAME

26:44.777 --> 26:46.779
AS YOU FALL DEEPER
AND DEEPER ASLEEP.

26:48.998 --> 26:51.958
NOW, I WANT YOU TO LET YOUR
THOUGHTS DRIFT BACK IN TIME.

26:52.785 --> 26:54.613
BACK TO A TIME BEFORE THE FIRE.

26:57.746 --> 27:00.749
DADDY, DADDY, WAIT FOR ME.

27:01.358 --> 27:04.840
DADDY! DADDY, DADDY,
WAIT FOR ME.

27:05.536 --> 27:07.060
CAN I COME WITH?

27:07.190 --> 27:09.715
DADDY! DADDY, CAN I COME WITH?

27:11.194 --> 27:12.108
OKAY.

27:14.328 --> 27:17.287
HERE. HOLD ON TO THIS FOR ME
IN CASE I NEED IT.

27:19.333 --> 27:21.944
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

27:55.804 --> 27:58.720
[SORROWFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

28:20.002 --> 28:21.351
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

29:00.216 --> 29:01.740
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

30:08.067 --> 30:13.028
FOWLER

30:32.700 --> 30:36.399
[MUSIC PLAYING]

30:37.357 --> 30:41.317
ONE, TWO, THREE.

30:41.927 --> 30:43.189
OPEN YOUR EYES.

30:52.415 --> 30:55.766
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

31:07.430 --> 31:11.478
[PANTING]

31:36.851 --> 31:40.246
[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

31:42.552 --> 31:43.814
YEAH, LET'S GO IN.

31:45.164 --> 31:47.079
RESTRICTED AREA
KEEP OUT

31:53.824 --> 31:55.435
LET'S MAKE A TAKE OFF RAMP.

31:55.565 --> 31:57.437
BUT YOUR DAD'S WAITING FOR US
AT THE BEACH.

31:57.567 --> 31:59.004
NAH, HE'S FISHIN'.

31:59.134 --> 32:00.788
DOESN'T NOTICE ANYTHING
WHEN HE'S FISHIN'.

32:01.397 --> 32:03.704
COME ON. JUST A COUPLE OF JUMPS.

32:08.491 --> 32:10.276
[GRUNTING]

32:15.629 --> 32:17.457
[SCREAMING]

32:17.587 --> 32:18.588
MARK!

32:20.068 --> 32:22.723
MARK! MARK,
ARE YOU OKAY DOWN THERE?

32:23.332 --> 32:25.944
MARK, SAY SOMETHING! MARK!

32:38.782 --> 32:40.088
FEEL BETTER?

32:40.219 --> 32:41.611
AH, I DUNNO HOW I FEEL.

32:43.222 --> 32:47.269
LEARNING ABOUT MY DAD LIKE THAT.
THE WAY HE DIED.

32:47.400 --> 32:48.923
LOGAN, YOUR DAD DIED A HERO.

32:49.054 --> 32:50.055
I KNOW.

32:50.664 --> 32:52.361
AND I DIDN'T EVEN REMEMBER HIM.

32:53.145 --> 32:57.149
AND GIVEN THE OPPORTUNITY
TO BE LIKE HIM, I JUST FROZE.

32:58.759 --> 32:59.716
BUT YOU DIDN'T.

33:01.022 --> 33:02.676
YOU WENT INTO THE BOAT
JUST LIKE HE DID.

33:03.633 --> 33:05.548
AND YOU RISKED YOUR LIFE
TO SAVE A STRANGER.

33:05.766 --> 33:08.290
THAT'S WHAT WE DO.
WE'RE LIFEGUARDS.

33:08.421 --> 33:10.989
HMM. BUT DAD WAS A LOT LIKE YOU.

33:12.903 --> 33:15.254
WELL, IF YOU'RE LOOKIN'
FOR A FATHER FIGURE, FORGET IT.

33:15.384 --> 33:18.039
I'VE ALREADY GOT ONE
DEFIANT REBEL ON MY HANDS.

33:18.344 --> 33:20.302
NAH, I'VE GOT A FATHER NOW.

33:21.303 --> 33:24.567
I JUST GOTTA FIND OUT MORE ABOUT
WHO HE WAS.

33:25.438 --> 33:27.962
YEAH. EXPECT SURPRISES.

33:28.571 --> 33:31.661
MISTER HOWARD! MISTER HOWARD!

33:32.401 --> 33:33.837
MISTER HOWARD! MISTER HOWARD!

33:34.838 --> 33:36.449
MISTER HOWARD!

33:36.579 --> 33:38.494
-WHAT? WHAT DO YOU WANT?
-MARK FELL IN A HOLE UP THERE.

33:38.625 --> 33:40.322
-WHERE? WHERE?
-UP HERE!

33:40.453 --> 33:41.410
LET'S GO!

33:41.541 --> 33:43.978
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

33:46.459 --> 33:48.939
[SIREN WAILING]

34:05.521 --> 34:07.393
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

34:08.263 --> 34:11.223
[SIREN WAILING]

34:12.092 --> 34:14.094
COME ON, EVERYBODY BACK.
COME ON.

34:14.226 --> 34:16.184
MARK! MARK, IT'S DAD!
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

34:16.315 --> 34:18.491
MARK, CAN YOU HERE ME? IT'S DAD!

34:18.621 --> 34:20.623
-MARK! MARK!
-COME ON, STEP BACK.

34:20.754 --> 34:22.321
WE DON'T WANT
TWO OF YOU GUYS DOWN THERE.

34:22.625 --> 34:24.279
YOU DIDN'T SEE THE SIGN?
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

34:24.409 --> 34:25.367
SORRY.

34:25.498 --> 34:26.803
HE'S NOT MOVING.

34:28.327 --> 34:30.719
HE'S GOTTA BE AT LEAST
20 FEET DOWN THERE.

34:30.851 --> 34:31.764
LOWER ME DOWN. I'LL GET HIM.

34:31.895 --> 34:32.766
NO, NO, NO. I'LL GET HIM.

34:32.896 --> 34:34.333
THE HOLE'S TOO NARROW.

34:34.463 --> 34:35.768
-YOU WON'T FIT.
-I'LL GET HIM. HOOK ME UP.

34:36.291 --> 34:37.771
HERE'S A JUMPSUIT.

34:38.815 --> 34:41.775
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

34:58.052 --> 35:00.272
-HE'S ALIVE.
-HE'S STILL ALIVE, ISN'T HE?

35:00.402 --> 35:02.448
YEAH, HE'S STILL ALIVE,
DON'T WORRY. WE'LL GET HIM OUT.

35:03.275 --> 35:04.363
OKAY, EVERYTHING SET?

35:04.493 --> 35:06.060
EVERYTHING'S SET.

35:06.191 --> 35:07.366
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S DO IT.
-ANYTHING I CAN DO TO HELP?

35:07.496 --> 35:09.063
YEAH, JUST FEED ME
SOME LINE THERE.

35:10.020 --> 35:11.848
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

35:12.588 --> 35:13.894
[GRUNTING]

35:14.851 --> 35:17.550
[CROWD TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

35:20.161 --> 35:21.206
[GRUNTING]

35:26.124 --> 35:26.994
FURTHER.

35:27.125 --> 35:28.300
ALL RIGHT.

35:33.522 --> 35:34.654
FURTHER.

35:38.832 --> 35:40.007
A LITTLE FURTHER.

35:44.751 --> 35:46.013
KEEP GOING.

35:52.759 --> 35:54.543
OKAY. I SEE HIM.

35:54.674 --> 35:55.762
ALL RIGHT.

35:58.112 --> 35:59.069
[GRUNTING]

36:00.288 --> 36:01.420
OKAY, THERE. STOP.

36:06.033 --> 36:07.121
[GRUNTING]

36:14.084 --> 36:15.347
HE'S GOT A PULSE.

36:15.956 --> 36:17.610
[CHUCKLING]

36:17.740 --> 36:19.916
[CROWD MURMURING]

36:20.526 --> 36:22.876
MARK! MARK!

36:23.006 --> 36:24.269
HOW YOU DOIN', MATE?

36:24.965 --> 36:27.881
YOU OKAY?
CAN YOU MOVE YOUR ARMS AND LEGS?

36:29.012 --> 36:30.666
YEAH? CAN YOU MOVE THEM?

36:32.059 --> 36:33.147
HE SEEMS TO BE OKAY.

36:33.278 --> 36:35.758
[CROWD MURMURING]

36:35.889 --> 36:37.456
OKAY, GRAB MY HAND.
GRAB MY HAND.

36:39.719 --> 36:41.155
-OKAY, YOU ALL RIGHT?
-YEAH.

36:41.590 --> 36:42.809
OKAY, GRAB MY WRIST.

36:43.984 --> 36:45.333
TAKE YOU UP NICE AND SLOW.

36:45.464 --> 36:46.856
TAKE ME UP!

36:46.987 --> 36:48.510
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S BRING HIM UP REAL SLOW.

36:48.641 --> 36:49.598
HERE WE GO.

36:50.251 --> 36:51.383
[GRUNTING]

36:51.513 --> 36:54.168
[CROWD MURMURING]

37:04.134 --> 37:05.832
HOLD ON. THAT'S A BOY.

37:09.270 --> 37:11.577
[GRUNTING]

37:15.233 --> 37:16.234
AH!

37:17.147 --> 37:18.540
HEY! ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

37:19.802 --> 37:20.760
YOU ALL RIGHT?

37:21.891 --> 37:24.285
GRAB MY HAND! GRAB MY HAND!

37:24.416 --> 37:26.809
IT'S OKAY. KEEP PULLING!

37:26.940 --> 37:31.205
[CROWD MURMURING]

37:31.336 --> 37:34.339
[GRUNTING]

37:42.129 --> 37:44.000
I SEE HIM. I GOT HIM.

37:44.131 --> 37:45.872
HERE HE COMES. HERE WE GO.

37:46.699 --> 37:49.223
[CROWD EXCLAIMING]

37:52.531 --> 37:53.488
HE'S OKAY, MITCH.

37:57.057 --> 38:00.190
WAY TO GO, LOGAN.
YOUR DAD WOULD BE PROUD.

38:00.930 --> 38:02.410
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT? ARE YOU OKAY?

38:03.106 --> 38:04.673
-THANKS!
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:04.804 --> 38:05.718
-THANKS.
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:07.937 --> 38:10.200
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

38:13.378 --> 38:16.032
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

38:20.646 --> 38:22.735
OH, IT'S A SCRAPBOOK.

38:22.865 --> 38:24.171
NO, NO, NO, NO, LOOK.

38:24.302 --> 38:25.651
IT'S MUCH MORE
THAN JUST A SCRAPBOOK.

38:28.393 --> 38:30.046
LOOK AT THE WAY
EVERYTHING'S LAID OUT.

38:31.047 --> 38:32.832
THE MOUNTING'S
JUST PERFECT, HUH?

38:33.528 --> 38:35.269
THE SENSE OF DESIGN
AND CONTINUITY,

38:35.400 --> 38:36.705
I MEAN, THAT'S STUFF
MY DAD WAS GOOD AT.

38:36.836 --> 38:38.446
OH, THIS IS SO GREAT.

38:38.577 --> 38:40.056
YOUR DAD MUST'VE BEEN
SO PROUD OF YOU TO DO THIS.

38:40.187 --> 38:42.407
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK.
MY FIRST RESCUE CARD, HUH.

38:43.190 --> 38:45.018
ISN'T THAT AWESOME?

38:45.148 --> 38:46.933
THE WAY HE PUT IN A TOWER AND
THE SUN-- HEY, DON'T TOUCH IT!

38:47.063 --> 38:48.369
-SORRY.
-GET YOUR FINGERPRINTS ON IT.

38:48.500 --> 38:49.631
WHAT ARE YOU, CRAZY?

38:49.762 --> 38:50.893
I'M CLEAN.

38:51.111 --> 38:52.765
I KNOW IT'S LATE IN PARIS, MOM,

38:52.895 --> 38:55.550
BUT UM, THIS PHONE CALL'S
A COUPLE DAYS LATE,

38:55.681 --> 38:59.206
AND I WANTED TO WISH
DAD A HAPPY FATHER'S DAY.

39:00.163 --> 39:01.034
THANKS.

39:03.341 --> 39:04.342
PAPA?

39:05.168 --> 39:11.087
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

39:27.495 --> 39:28.583
[SIGHING]

39:34.023 --> 39:35.373
SO WHAT DID YOUR MOM SAY

39:35.503 --> 39:37.592
WHEN YOU TOLD HER
THAT YOU REMEMBERED?

39:38.767 --> 39:42.771
THAT SHE WAS RELIEVED AND SORRY.

39:43.511 --> 39:46.645
BUT THAT AFTER THE EXPLOSION,
I BLOCKED THE WHOLE THING OUT.

39:47.994 --> 39:50.692
SAYS SHE TOLD EVERYBODY NEVER
TO EVER MENTION IT TO ME AGAIN.

39:53.303 --> 39:54.870
AS I GOT OLDER, I GUESS...

39:56.394 --> 39:58.570
I BLOCKED OUT ALL MEMORIES
OF MY FATHER COMPLETELY.

40:01.311 --> 40:02.965
DID SHE TELL YOU ABOUT HIM?

40:03.183 --> 40:04.097
YEAH.

40:05.968 --> 40:08.057
SHE'S SENDING ME
A TRUNK OF ALL OF HIS OLD STUFF.

40:10.582 --> 40:12.061
HOW DOES THAT MAKE YOU FEEL?

40:14.760 --> 40:15.804
NERVOUS, A LITTLE.

40:19.504 --> 40:21.157
BUT I'M LOOKING FORWARD
TO KNOWING HIM.

40:22.811 --> 40:26.772
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

40:35.737 --> 40:37.826
SOMETIMES WE FORGET
THE MOST IMPORTANT MOMENTS

40:37.957 --> 40:39.175
OF OUR CHILDHOOD.

40:40.699 --> 40:43.789
MOM SAID I WAS THREE WHEN DAD
FIRST BROUGHT ME TO THE BEACH.

40:44.442 --> 40:46.095
SHE SAID I WAS SO SCARED
OF THE WAVES

40:46.226 --> 40:47.619
I WOULDN'T
GET OFF HIS SHOULDERS.

40:47.749 --> 40:49.185
SO WHAT'D HE DO?

40:49.316 --> 40:51.013
WELL, SHE SAID HE WALKED OUT
INTO THE WATER

40:51.144 --> 40:52.493
'TIL IT WAS ABOVE HIS HEAD

40:52.624 --> 40:55.235
AND HELD ME THERE
UNTIL I STOPPED CRYIN'.

40:56.279 --> 40:59.326
AFTER THAT, LOVED THE OCEAN.

41:00.240 --> 41:02.808
I HOPE I ALWAYS REMEMBER THESE
TIMES WE SPEND TOGETHER, DAD.

41:02.938 --> 41:04.853
THEN, WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE MAKE IT MEMORABLE?

41:04.984 --> 41:05.854
ALL RIGHT!

41:06.638 --> 41:07.769
LET'S GO!

41:13.296 --> 41:15.255
WOO! ALL RIGHT!

41:16.343 --> 41:19.694
-YEAH! OH, YEAH!
-WHOA!

41:20.521 --> 41:22.262
-HANG ON.
-ALL RIGHT, I GOTCHA.

41:22.392 --> 41:24.482
[LAUGHING]

41:25.221 --> 41:26.658
YOU AND ME, PAL.

41:27.180 --> 41:28.964
-WHOA!
-IT'S YOU AND ME.

41:31.314 --> 41:33.578
[LAUGHING]

41:35.014 --> 41:39.014
[ENDING MUSIC]
